#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:1
msgid "Object manager"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:3
msgid "Serialization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:4
msgid ""
"You can register objects with a `vtkObjectManager` instance and call "
"`UpdateStatesFromObjects`, `GetState(identifier)` to obtain a serialized "
"state of the registered objects and all their dependency objects that are "
"serializable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:9
msgid "Deserialization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:10
msgid ""
"You can register a json state (stringified) with a `vtkObjectManager` "
"instance and call `UpdateObjectsFromStates`, `GetObjectAtId(identifier)` to "
"deserialize and retrieve the objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:14
msgid "Blobs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:15
msgid ""
"All `vtkDataArray` are hashed and stored as unique blobs to prevent multiple "
"copies of the same data within the state. The contents of a data array "
"within a state are represented with a hash string. You can fetch and "
"register blobs using `GetBlob` and `RegisterBlob`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:20
msgid "Dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:21
msgid ""
"You can retrieve all dependent object identifiers using `vtkObjectManager::"
"GetAllDependencies(identifier)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:24
msgid "Extensions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:25
msgid ""
"You can also (de)serialize classes in custom VTK modules. Simply pass the "
"registrar function to `vtkObjectManager::"
"InitializeExtensionModuleHandler(registrar)` where the `registrar` argument "
"is of type `vtkSessionObjectManagerRegistrarFunc`. In C/C++, this function "
"can be accessed from the `vtkModuleNameSerDes.h` header file in your build "
"directory. In Python, this function is available as an attribute on the "
"module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:31
msgid "Here are examples:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:33
msgid ""
"#include <vtkFooSerDes.h>\n"
"\n"
"vtkNew<vtkObjectManager> manager;\n"
"manager->InitializeExtensionModuleHandler(RegisterClasses_vtkFoo);\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:40
msgid ""
"from vtkmodules import vtkInteractionWidgets\n"
"from vtkmodules.vtkSerializationManager import vtkObjectManager\n"
"object_manager = vtkObjectManager()\n"
"object_manager.InitializeExtensionModuleHandler(vtkInteractionWidgets."
"RegisterClasses_vtkInteractionWidgets)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:47
msgid "Serialization of addon in WASM"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:49
msgid ""
"In WASM, you will need to create two directories that resemble this tree. In "
"this illustration, we wish to (de)serialize classes from the `Bar` and `Foo` "
"modules in WASM using `vtkRemoteSession` or `vtkStandaloneSession`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:52
msgid ""
"The `WebAssemblyAsync` module is optional. You can leave it out if you are "
"not interested in having WebGPU support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:55
msgid ""
"- Bar\n"
" |- ...\n"
" |- vtk.module\n"
"- Foo\n"
" |- ...\n"
" |- vtk.module\n"
"- WebAssembly\n"
" |- vtk.module\n"
" |- CMakeLists.txt\n"
"- WebAssemblyAsync\n"
" |- vtk.module\n"
" |- CMakeLists.txt\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:70
msgid "Declare your dependencies in `WebAssembly/vtk.module`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:72
msgid ""
"NAME\n"
"  FooBar::WebAssembly\n"
"LIBRARY_NAME\n"
"  fooBarWebAssembly\n"
"PRIVATE_DEPENDS\n"
"  VTK::SerializationManager\n"
"  VTK::WebAssemblySession\n"
"OPTIONAL_DEPENDS\n"
"  FooBar::Foo\n"
"  FooBar::Bar\n"
"  VTK::RenderingContextOpenGL2\n"
"  VTK::RenderingOpenGL2\n"
"  VTK::RenderingUI\n"
"  VTK::RenderingVolumeOpenGL2\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:89
msgid "Build the module in the `WebAssembly/CMakeLists.txt`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:91
msgid ""
"if (NOT CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME STREQUAL \"Emscripten\")\n"
"  message(FATAL_ERROR\n"
"    \"The VTK::WebAssembly module requires Emscripten compiler.\")\n"
"endif ()\n"
"\n"
"vtk_module_add_serdes_wasm_package(\n"
"  MODULE FooBar::WebAssembly\n"
"  OUTPUT_NAME fooBarWebAssembly\n"
")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:103
msgid ""
"Finally, ensure the `WebAssembly/vtk.module` is passed to `vtk_module_build` "
"in your project's root `CMakeLists.txt`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:105
msgid ""
"If you are interested in WebGPU support, declare your dependencies in "
"`WebAssemblyAsync/vtk.module` and repeat similar steps as in the non-async "
"section using the new module names."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/object_manager.md:108
msgid ""
"NAME\n"
"  FooBar::WebAssemblyAsync\n"
"LIBRARY_NAME\n"
"  fooBarWebAssemblyAsync\n"
"PRIVATE_DEPENDS\n"
"  VTK::SerializationManager\n"
"  VTK::WebAssemblySession\n"
"OPTIONAL_DEPENDS\n"
"  FooBar::Foo\n"
"  FooBar::Bar\n"
"  VTK::RenderingContextOpenGL2\n"
"  VTK::RenderingOpenGL2\n"
"  VTK::RenderingUI\n"
"  VTK::RenderingVolumeOpenGL2\n"
"  VTK::RenderingWebGPU\n"
msgstr ""
